{"label":"Poems Collection - 3","id":"poems-collection-3","lockAfter":1,"list":[{"id":"100","type":"passage","label":"Listen","data":{"title":"Listen","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"Listen now dear\nWhat your heart \nTells you to do\nDo it with love\nBe it a drawing\nBe it a play\nDo what you want\nTo be your best\nAnd it is a must"}},{"id":"200","type":"passage","label":"On the way","data":{"title":"On the way","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"I am on the way\nMy way to the land\nWhere it is spring\nFlapping my wings\nI fly on my way\nWhen winter sets in\nMaking everything cold\nBirds decide to fly\nTo reach a warm home\nWith food to eat\nAnd a place to sleep!\nTo hatch new eggs\nTo raise our chicks\nWe fly thousands of miles\nAnd reach with a smile!"}},{"id":"300","type":"passage","label":"On the street","data":{"title":"On the street","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"Bark, bark, bark\nAll night they bark\nMaking everyone\nNot to have sleep\nDogs roam at night\nAnd chase each other\nWhatever it may be\nAwake through the night\nDogs bark and bark\nWhen morning sets in\nDogs find a place\nTo curl and sleep"}},{"id":"400","type":"passage","label":"My day","data":{"title":"My day","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"It is my day\nTo be happy today\nSweet laddoos\nHot, hot vadas\nMummy makes them\nFor me \nAnd my friends\nTo eat and play\nFor today\nIs our holiday."}},{"id":"500","type":"passage","label":"Swing","data":{"title":"Swing","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"We all play\nSwinging every day\nOn the swing\nFrom the branch\nOf our neem tree\nSwish goes it\nHigh up in the air\nAnd then comes down\nIs it not fair\nTo wait for my turn\nTill my friend\nCompletes another round"}},{"id":"600","type":"passage","label":"A Butterfly","data":{"title":"A Butterfly","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"A colorful butterfly\nFlies in my garden\nGoing from one flower \nTo another flower \nTo taste sweet nectar\nWith pollen on petals\nIt flies in the morning\nIt flies in the evening\nAnd sleeps in the night\nOn a bed of leaves."}},{"id":"700","type":"passage","label":"A Visitor","data":{"title":"A Visitor","type":"poem","lineGap":"5px","author":"Kalai Selvi","text":"On a day last week\nWhen a light rain\nStarted to bring in\nA weather so comfortable\nA strange visitor\nKnocked our doors\n“Knock, knock, knock\nIs there someone there”\nI peeped through\nThe hole on the door \nSurprise I opened the door\nFor a little dinosaur\nStood there with a look\nFor he wanted me \nTo give my painting brush\nTo draw a picture\nThat looked like me!"}}]}